The paper focuses on the design and development of security-focused automation for software development, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The approach presented in the paper involves the use of neural networks, specifically convolutional neural networks, to identify security-related content in software issue tracking systems. This involves natural language processing and semantic ontology, which could also fall under the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also evaluates the approach on a commercial software project, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) category.
